dal_main_2532005\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104siz1665702981103.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/siz1665702981103.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/siz1665702981103.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"siz1665702981103\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Determining the Display Device\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"siz1665702981103__determining_the_display_device_189266\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface use the several mechanisms to determine which device translation table to use for display.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"siz1665702981103__li_d27569e1_d27570e1_d27571e1\">Assignment files—if the device translation table you want to use is not in the default library (USYS), the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$VARIATION</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DISPLAY</span> settings must specify the library and device translation table to use for screen output.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63317e1_d63318e1_d63319e1\">If specific applications use different values, it is better to define them in a Uniface assignment file than rely on the other mechanisms.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"siz1665702981103__li_d27572e1_d27573e1_d27574e1\">Environment variables—the UDISP variable, if defined, overrides the system default for the display device.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63320e1_d63321e1_d63322e1\">If the devices used are applicable for everyone at your site, it is advisable to use operating system symbols to define the assignments. These assignments should be placed in a system-wide logon script, if there is one. Refer to the documentation for your operating system to see how to do this.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"siz1665702981103__li_d27575e1_d27576e1_d27577e1\">Operating system defaults—for example, on Unix the\n                                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">TERM</code> environment variable indicates\n                                terminal being used.  <p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63323e1_d63324e1_d63325e1\">If no\n                                        other assignments are present, Uniface uses the default\n                                        obtained from the operating system to determine the device\n                                        translation table used.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"siz1665702981103__topic_d41747e1_d41748e1_d41749e1_d41750e1_d41751e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d850515e83\">\n                       \n Setting UDISP\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63329e1_d63330e1_d63331e1\">The UDISP symbol overrides the system display default. It has different names under each operating system and is set in different ways. For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"siz1665702981103__li_d27578e1_d27579e1_d27580e1\">Under Windows, set the UDISP environment variable.\n \n            </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"siz1665702981103__li_d27581e1_d27582e1_d27583e1\">Under the Unix shell <code class=\"ph codeph\">(sh)</code>, use the following command to set the environment variable:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">UDISP=SUN;export UDISP\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63332e1_d63333e1_d63334e1\">Uppercase variables have priority over lowercase ones.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"siz1665702981103__p_d63335e1_d63336e1_d63337e1\">Refer to the operating system documentation for details.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532005\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532005\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Determining the Display Device Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determining the Display Device Uniface use the several mechanisms to determine which device translation table to use for display. Assignment files—if the device translation table you want to use is not in the default library (USYS), the $VARIATION and $DISPLAY settings must specify the library and device translation table to use for screen output. If specific applications use different values, it is better to define them in a Uniface assignment file than rely on the other mechanisms. Environment variables—the UDISP variable, if defined, overrides the system default for the display device. If the devices used are applicable for everyone at your site, it is advisable to use operating system symbols to define the assignments. These assignments should be placed in a system-wide logon script, if there is one. Refer to the documentation for your operating system to see how to do this. Operating system defaults—for example, on Unix the TERM environment variable indicates terminal being used. If no other assignments are present, Uniface uses the default obtained from the operating system to determine the device translation table used. Setting UDISP The UDISP symbol overrides the system display default. It has different names under each operating system and is set in different ways. For example: Under Windows, set the UDISP environment variable. Under the Unix shell (sh) , use the following command to set the environment variable: UDISP=SUN;export UDISP Copy Uppercase variables have priority over lowercase ones. Refer to the operating system documentation for details. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}